abstract: The Circuit of the Americas is only a year old, but because its design incorporates some favorite elements from other circuits, it seems familiar.
snippet: The Circuit of the Americas is only a year old, but because its design incorporates some favorite elements from other circuits, it seems familiar.
lead_paragraph: Because the design of the Circuit of the Americas in Austin, Texas, incorporates many favorite corners and features from other racing tracks on the Formula One calendar, it is already well-loved by drivers, engineers and spectators.
headline_main: Austin’s ‘Classic’ Track Wins Over Fans and Drivers
headline_print_headline: New 'Classic' Track Wins Over Fans and Drivers

abstract: USA plans to announce a deal for a new TV drama, “Dig,” centering on archaeological discoveries in Jerusalem’s Old City.
snippet: USA plans to announce a deal for a new TV drama, “Dig,” centering on archaeological discoveries in Jerusalem’s Old City.
lead_paragraph: In recent years, executives at the USA Network have stood on the sidelines, watching cable dramas like AMC’s “Breaking Bad” and Showtime’s “Homeland” collect the critical raves and awards. Now they want to get into the game.

abstract: The author and master contrarian left his entire estate to Harvard, forsaking loved ones and setting off a legal battle.
snippet: The author and master contrarian left his entire estate to Harvard, forsaking loved ones and setting off a legal battle.
lead_paragraph: Gore Vidal always kept a fire burning in the grate, his nephew Burr Steers said as we stood in the author’s living room in Los Angeles, “even when it was 110 degrees outside.” Mr. Vidal had suffered hypothermia while serving in the Army during World War II, Mr. Steers added, and his left knee was made of titanium.

lead_paragraph: 9 P.M. (13) LOU REED: ROCK AND ROLL HEART (1998) The director Timothy Greenfield-Sanders tours Mr. Reed’s career, from his days with the Velvet Underground and denizen of Warhol’s Factory to his solo work and collaboration with Robert Wilson. The film also touches on dark side of Mr. Reed, above, but “is careful to note that he has gone past all that,” Caryn James wrote in The New York Times about this “American Masters” presentation. “And though the documentary takes too much at face value, Mr. Reed himself sounds more sophisticated about how public image and reality bleed together. ‘I’m not remotely really like the Lou Reed character that I managed to make on record, although after a while I thought he was so cool that I thought it might be fun to be him, so I did,’ he says. He later points out that in the ’80s he married and started going to A.A. Having cleaned up his act no doubt certifies him as PBS ready.” Mr. Reed died at 71 on Oct. 27.

abstract: By using unique magnets in its electric motors, KLD Energy Technologies says it can power neighborhood electric vehicles with smaller, lower-voltage batteries.
snippet: By using unique magnets in its electric motors, KLD Energy Technologies says it can power neighborhood electric vehicles with smaller, lower-voltage batteries.
lead_paragraph: DESERT HOT SPRINGS, Calif. — If only electric propulsion could operate at low voltage, maximize the motor’s performance and do without the cumbersome array of batteries. That’s the proposition advanced by KLD Energy Technologies of Austin, Tex., which suggests that it has come up with the next great innovation in electric-vehicle powertrains.

abstract: Although surging sales for the minivan are a distant memory — Americans bought 1.37 million in 2000 — the vehicle has found its niche.
snippet: Although surging sales for the minivan are a distant memory — Americans bought 1.37 million in 2000 — the vehicle has found its niche.
lead_paragraph: THE minivan was a cliché almost from the moment the first Dodge Caravan rolled off Chrysler’s assembly line in 1983. It was the boxy family hauler aimed at harried soccer moms, a symbol of the soul-crushing conformity that was the price Americans paid for suburban comfort.
